Entry.P:
Congestive heart failure or exacerbation
of (chest pain; shortness of breath; troubled breathing,
tightness in chest, and/or wheezing; decrease in amount of urine;
swelling of face, fingers, feet, or lower legs; unusual tiredness;
weight gain)

Thrombocytopenia, with or without purpura (usually asymptomatic;
rarely, unusual bleeding or bruising; black, tarry stools; blood
in urine or stools; pinpoint red spots on skin)
